{
  "stem": "1169.2",
  "chunk_idx": 4,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.0,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 27,
      "text": "And this baby is, thank God, alive today.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 28,
      "text": "And he is, in fact, a Hasidic rabbi in Williamsburg.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 29,
      "text": "He lives his call today, that [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 30,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] I was at his bris, at his circumcision, eight days later, which was also in the shul.",
      "word_count": 21
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 31,
      "text": "And they gave permission to have this.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 32,
      "text": "And at that time, in our city was also locked up a rabbi who became very prominent now, was the rabbi of a village near us called [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 28
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 33,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 3 SECONDS] And he came from a Hasidic dynasty, the Teitelbaum family.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 34,
      "text": "And my father asked they should let him out for a few hours, which they did.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 35,
      "text": "And he had the honor of being the sandek, the one who holds the baby during the circumcision.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 36,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] And my father, as always, took me to be part of this.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 37,
      "text": "We took-- we got together 10 people, a minion.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 38,
      "text": "And the bris was there.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 39,
      "text": "Afterwards, everybody cried bitterly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 40,
      "text": "And everybody made a statement that was-- really impressed me, and-- and-- impressed me and depressed me.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 41,
      "text": "They said, well now his fate is sealed.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 42,
      "text": "That was the statement.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 43,
      "text": "Instead of-- usually at the bris, there is a joyous environment.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 44,
      "text": "This was a very sad moment.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 45,
      "text": "His fate is sealed.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 46,
      "text": "My father cried bitterly.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 47,
      "text": "Also, this rabbi of [NON-ENGLISH], who today is known as the rabbi of Satmar, cried bitterly.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "When my dad and him met later in the United States, he asked my father.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He said, [NON-ENGLISH], Rabbi of [NON-ENGLISH], you cried so at this bris.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Did you know what's happening to us?",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "Did you know where they are taking us?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And my father told him, no.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "I didn't know where they are taking us, but I know it's not a good place.",
      "word_count": 16
    }
  ],
